"children":[
"Microscopic colitis is characterized by chronic diarrhea, sometimes accompanied by mild abdominal pain and weight loss, most commonly in women aged 45 to 60 years, and is associated with other autoimmune conditions, particularly celiac disease."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s15_2",
